H3 There is also a port to Windows which will run in a console window. This is useful if you want to do any work from the command line or via a remote login, which I‚Äôll admit is unlikely for Windows. While fully functional, the main purpose of this version is for scripting, allowing you to convert documents and run user scripts.
P Italics, bold and underline are displayed as various colours.
P The console version is called cwordgrinder.exe and is installed next to the main WordGrinder executable. I expect that if you want to use this, you know how to find it.
